Text.Value: I'm fine. Let's talk about the future.
And what a gift you've been to me, to keep our flame burning even when the winds of change threaten to blow it out.
But I can't abandon you either. Return to Avernus - for now - and I'll join you once the city's been put to rights after this disaster.
The people I'm sworn to protect will see only an illithid. They would cower in fear - or worse yet, try to fill you with arrows and daggers.
This is where we part ways, Wyll.
All right, Wyll. All right. I'll go.
I want you to see my blade slice her wings off her back, to hear her groans as she dissolves into ash.
They would never see you as the hero I know you to be. They would only see a mind flayer.
Ha! You've already thought about a little Ravengard running around, have you?
No, it's too dangerous. Zariel's forces would crush us.
You promised yourself to me for an eternity...
*A moment passes. Wylls eyes glance up to his horns.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: A moment passes. Wylls eyes glance upwards.

Text.Value: I see it in your eyes. The time is near.
Raphael's set his sights on Zariel's throne. She'll be too busy fighting him to pursue you.
I'll bring you anything you need - robes, books... sustenance. You'll be safe.
I'd like that. Let's do it.
For the first time, I have a future. I want to share it with you.
We'll make a place for you in the undercity, a secluded corner of your own. I'll bring you anything you need - robes, books... sustenance. You'll be safe.

EditorData.NodeContext: Sustenance = brains, so a bit of hesitation there

Text.Value: It pains me to know you must live this half-life, hidden in shadows when you deserve to bask in the Sword Coast's sun.
I think it's better if I'm on my own.
No. I won't go back. I can't. Anything but that.
I can't force you, Karlach. And if you'd rather go now - here - I suppose I have no choice but to respect it, though it breaks my heart in two.
The people of Baldur's Gate will accept a devil as a duke - but they'd never accept his mind flayer consort.
I understand. Your duty is to the Sword Coast.
What a joy, this life we're about to make, this story we're about to write - every chapter more thrilling than the last.
I was selfish to ask you to live a half-life as a plaything for the Blade of Avernus. And even more selfish, to be disappointed by your answer.
I would never.
I'm not Gortash. I don't want to instil fear, I want to instil hope. Hope for a bountiful future, hope for a life free of tyranny and torment -
Let's do it, then. I'll join you in the Hells and help kill Mizora.
I've been too afraid even to think of returning. But with you, I can face it. Let's do it, Wyll.
I'm myself for the first time, you're impossibly brilliant. Together we will be unstoppable.
Let's leave reason to the soft-hearted - the Nightsinger will want me to keep my skills sharp.
You need closure - I understand that. Mizora won't stand a chance against us.
I couldn't be more ready. Let's descend to the Hells and kill Mizora.
You promised yourself to me for an eternity...
Maybe you're right. Maybe I should go back.
I must demonstrate to Lady Shar the value of our union. A grand wedding is in order - a show of power.
I think a grand wedding is in order. I have a feeling I might look good in white.
A grand wedding is in order. I want to show off my groom to the city.
Raphael's set his sights on Zariel's throne. She'll be too busy fighting him to pursue you.
A reasonable person would say 'no'. I still want you to say 'yes'.
*Sigh* If only last night could have lasted forever. How are you feeling, my darling?
*Yet of one thing, you are most certain: whatever comes next, you'll face it alone.*
I'd like that. Let's do it.
You're on your own.
Please let her go. For me, for us, for the good of Faerûn.
Perhaps one day you'll change your mind - but if you won't, at least know this:
All I can ask then is - wait for me. If you can't, if you won't, then know this:
I can't. I'm responsible for Baldur's Gate. She needs me - desperately, now more than ever. I can't abandon her.
I must not neglect my duties to Lady Shar... but she will want me to keep my skills honed. Let us hunt.
And here was me, thinking I'd settle into the quiet life. I suppose that can wait a little longer... let us hunt.
Of course I'll join you. I thought you'd never ask!
I cured the Urge. I want a free future, even if I look like this.
You've made me a new man.
*You detect the slightest hint of sorrow behind Wyll's words. The hellish fate that awaits him is never far from his mind.*
*Sigh.* I must have played this conversation in my head a dozen times this tenday, and practised how I'd say 'no'.
Forget Mizora. The people of the Coast call to the Blade and his star. Are you ready to be their hero?
There he is - the great champion of Baldur's Gate. I'll gather the snares, you can fletch the arrows.
There she is - the great champion of Baldur's Gate. I'll gather the snares, you can fletch the arrows.
There they are - the great champion of Baldur's Gate. I'll gather the snares, you can fletch the arrows.
It is. But that doesn't mean I have to discard you like a rotted carcass.
A beautiful fantasy. If only I could wish it into being.
Try to contain the inferno threatening to consume you.
Oh, my love. I wish I could understand. But I respect your wishes. If this is your time, I will stand by your side.
I am a new man -
Karlach... is there really no other way? Now that you've reached the end of the line, do you still refuse to return to Avernus? To live?
Open the gates and welcome every last refugee who seeks sanctuary.
And a magnificent ball, I presume, for dancing the night away. You wear your finest, and I'll look for one of father's dress uniforms.
We'll make a place for you - somewhere secluded, somewhere you can call home.
Let's do it, then. I'll join you in the Hells and help kill Mizora.
All these years as the Blade - I've been called a champion. A hero. A legend. Names I never asked for, praise I never sought.
But you? You've earned the right to be called 'hero' a thousand times over. What a gift you've been to the Sword Coast.
*Your mind turns to the future. Does happiness lurk in the remote corners of the Coast? Does it lurk anywhere at all for one stuck in the skin of a monster?*
I hope we never have to turn to the final page.
I want you to join me. Warriors, lovers, guardians. Two champions as one.
I cured the Urge. I want a free future, even if I look like this.
Are you sure you're ready? Mizora drained you of your powers.
This doesn't have to be the end.
There's something I need to ask you. Something terrible, something greedy, something unreasonable.
First, we mourn. We bow our heads for the fallen, and honour them by pledging peace.
Are you sure you're ready? Mizora drained you of your powers.
I think it's better if I'm on my own.
I've been too afraid even to think of returning. But with you, I can face it. Let's do it, Wyll.
I'm myself for the first time, you're impossibly brilliant. Together we will be unstoppable.
Let's leave reason to the soft-hearted - the Nightsinger will want me to keep my skills sharp.
You need closure - I understand that. Mizora won't stand a chance against us.
I couldn't be more ready. Let's descend to the Hells and kill Mizora.
You won't be alone. I need to set Baldur's Gate to rights after this disaster, but once she's stable, I could join you. Hunt out devils - real devils - together.
Would you go with me?
An uneasy life awaits you. But know this:
You won't be alone. I need to set Baldur's Gate to rights after this disaster, but once she's stable, I could join you. Hunt out devils - real devils - together.
I hoped you'd say 'yes'.
A revenge quest? You're better than this, Wyll.
I'd rather die in my home than live - barely - in the place I hate.
I understand. Your duty is to the city.
It's the least we can give them: a future worth looking forward to.
*A moment passes. The corners of Wyll's mouth turn downwards before he smiles again.*

Text.Value: And what a gift you've been to me. What an honour to walk alongside a true legend.
Then you reignited my fires. When I'm at your side, I want for nothing.
But it warms me to I can always find you, dance with you, in the years to come.
It's not about me. It's about every desperate soul Mizora will recruit to the Blood War, every life she snuffs out on Zariel's whims.
The eternal burden of my pact. I certainly couldn't expect you to shoulder it too.
A beautiful fantasy. If only I could wish it into being.

Text.Value: I want you to join me. A reasonable person would say 'no'. I still want you to say 'yes'.
But I have faith in me, in us. We'll cut Mizora to ribbons before she can so much as groan Zariel's name.
But I can't. Not when I know deep down that you're right.
Nod.
Heh - I was selfish to ask. And even more selfish, to be disappointed by your answer.
I'm the Blade of Avernus. I swore to cleanse the Hells of the devils that threaten the Coast. And I know my first target:
I won't go back to the Undercity. Not after I know all the horrors I wrought there as the Temple's leader.
Try to contain the inferno threatening to consume you.
Courage. Insight. Strategy. Justice. The four pillars of power. Not an eldritch blast to be found.
What future, Karlach? A future without you in it is no future at all. Is there really no other way?
I - I don't know what to say. I was sure we'd be carving out a future together.
What a gift you've been to me. What an honour to know a true legend.
These are your battles to fight, not mine. But I'll always be here for you when you return.
When Mizora drained my warlock powers, it was if a blizzard froze me through.
Come, rest with me tonight. And next I see you, may that flame be raging even stronger.
I stand as Lady Shar's chosen; now I must secure my legacy. Family- a young mind to mould.
I was denied my family for so long... I think it's time I started one of my own.
I was thinking about adoption. A new family - free of Bhaal's taint.
I'd like to start a family.
For the first time, I have a future. I want to share it with you.
If father were here... he'd be so proud of you. Proud of us.
You know I can't go back. Zariel would crush me without a thought. I'd rather die here, at home, than in the Hells.
All right, Wyll. All right. I'll go.
Gods, you're so wonderful, my heart's near to bursting.
I won't go back to the Undercity. Not after I know all the horrors I wrought there as the Temple's leader.
- and I've got you to thank for it.
That is... how are you feeling, darling? You look... peaked.
- and in more ways than one.
Oh, my love. I wish I could understand. But I respect your wishes. If this is your time, I will stand by your side.
I want you to join me. I want you to live, Karlach. We can have a life together, even in Avernus. A real life.
Sod off. I don't want to be your dirty little secret.
I must not neglect my duties to Lady Shar... but she will want me to keep my skills honed. Let us hunt.
And here was me, thinking I'd settle into the quiet life. I suppose that can wait a little longer... let us hunt.
Of course I'll join you. I thought you'd never ask!
My shining star. Since I've known you, we've shed more blood than could ever fill the Chionthar. The wounds we sustained were the testament to our might.
What future, Karlach? A future without you in it is no future at all. Is there really no other way?
I can't. I just can't, Wyll. All I want is to see the sky one last time.
It's not what I wanted, but I'm willing to give it a try.
I am the Blade of Frontiers. I swore to protect the Coast from the monsters that prey on it.
*Your mind turns to the future. Where will you go, and how will you feed? Can you ever find stability stuck in the skin of a monster?*
Sod off. I don't want to be your dirty little secret.
Through you, I've been born anew.
I was selfish to ask you to live a half-life as a plaything for the Blade of Frontiers. And even more selfish, to be disappointed by your answer.
I'd like that. Someone to carry our name, learn the four pillars. If only father -
I can't, Wyll. I can't go back. I'd rather die here, in my home, than go back there. All I want is to see the sky one last time.
A duke I'm soon to be - but the Blade's heart is never far from the frontiers.
*Your mind turns to the turbulent future. Does happiness lurk in the bowels of the city? Does it lurk anywhere at all for a man stuck in the skin of a monster?*
*Your mind turns to the turbulent future. Does happiness lurk in the bowels of the city? Does it lurk anywhere at all for a woman stuck in the skin of a monster?*
*Your mind turns to the future. Does happiness lurk in the bowels of the city? Does it lurk anywhere at all for one stuck in the skin of a monster?*
Mizora.
I love you. But I can't be with you. Not the way I wanted.
Anything for you, my love. Together, we'll cut the Hells in two. And Zariel will never lay a hand on you - I swear it.
And a magnificent ball, I presume, for dancing the night away. You dressed to the nines, me in the finest uniform I can convince father to lend me.
Declare your authority. March the Flaming Fist through the streets.
So be it. They'd lose nothing but power they hadn't yet gained. I'm not worried for them.
I'm fine. Let's talk about the future.
I see it in your eyes. The time is near.
Then we die proud, knowing we braved the Hells to slay the fiend who held my leash.
I was selfish to ask you to live a half-life as an underground plaything for a duke. And even more selfish, to be disappointed by your answer.
Father trained me in the sword and the bow. They'll have to sustain me.
I won't let her claim one more soul, slay one more victim. I'm going to make my way to the Hells and tear the horns right off her damned head.
Wherever you go, you take my heart with you. So strong is my love that not even a devil could break it.
I'll visit as often as I can. We can still dance, we can still write a story, we can still be us.
If you're by my side, I can do it. All right Wyll. We'll return to Avernus.
Please, Wyll - we can make this work.
An old-fashioned monster hunt, just the two of us.
Don't throw your life away, Karlach. Not like this.
So that's it? You'd just throw me away after the sacrifice that I made?
How could I ever refuse you?
Karlach... is there really no other way? Now that you've reached the end of the line, do you still refuse to return to Avernus? To live?
My star. The parasites have barely withered, your heart still hurts for them.
*Sigh* If only last night could have lasted forever. But if I'm to be a Grand Duke, I've got to greet the people and gain their trust.
I'm worried for every desperate soul Mizora will recruit to the Blood War, every life she snuffs out on Zariel's whims.
If we're meant to die, then let's do it together. Doing something worth dying for - hunting devils.
No. Just no.
But it warms me to know you'll be near.
But last night, I swear to you - your touch healed every one of my bruises and wiped away every scar.
Not good. I don't have long now.
It's not what I wanted, but I'm willing to give it a try.
I can't, Wyll, not while Mizora pulls the strings.
Now that you've reached the end of the line, do you still refuse to return to Avernus? To live?
After that, well - it's up to us to decide. Any ideas?
I meant it. And I still do.
*But in one thought, you find comfort: you don't have to face tomorrow alone.*
I'd rather die in my home than live - barely - in the place I hate. All I want is to see the sky one last time.
Would you go with me?
Wherever you go, you take my heart with you. So strong is my love that not even a devil could break it.
And why not name myself Archduke while I'm at it, maybe build some steel automatons to watch over the gates?
I knew you'd say 'yes'.
Maybe you're right. Maybe I should go back.

I am the Blade of Frontiers. I swore to protect the Coast from the monsters that prey on it. And I know my first target:
Please, Wyll - we can make this work.
Let it be done. The Jewel of the Coast will shine ever bright, welcoming the weak and the weary, from wherever they hail.
Well. Father would have loved having a grandchild. I know we'll raise a family worthy of his name.
So that's it? You'd just throw me away after the sacrifice that I made?
Next, we heal the city. We restore our broken buildings, stone by stone. We restore faith in each other, one good turn at a time.
Now that you've reached the end of the line, do you still refuse to return to Avernus? To live?
Say you'll come.
I'm the Blade of Avernus. I swore to cleanse the Hells of the devils that threaten the Coast.
So be it. The next we meet, my blade will stained with Mizora's blood.
Come. The next page in our saga begins.
I'd venture into the wilds with you at my side, if I could. 'The illithid who saved Baldur's Gate', I would cry, and the people would greet you as the hero I know you to be.
I'd parade you through the streets if I could. 'The illithid who saved Baldur's Gate', the bards would cry - and you would take your rightful place at the side of Grand Duke Wyll Ravengard.
I'd like that. So would father, I bet. A nipper to bear his name, learn the pillars. Courage, insight, strategy, justice.
- hope for leaders that won't turn their backs to suffering.
Not good. I don't have long now.
I'm sorry. The next we meet, my blade will stained with Mizora's blood.
Then this is goodbye. For now. Until we meet again, my love - I'll think of you every day. Now go. Live. You deserve that much.
Of course we can. And I know just how to do it.
I want you to join me. I want you to live, Karlach. We can have a life together, even in Avernus. A real life.

Synopsis:
Path in epilogue when players have one last moment with their romance partner.

Wyll could be
1. The Blade of Frontiers
2, The Blade of Avernus
3. Grand Duke

In all three cases, he may or may not be pacted, and he may or may not look like a devil.
